WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.104
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

00:06.172 --> 00:08.039
SY, ARE YOU
FORGETTING ANYTHING?

00:08.042 --> 00:09.475
NOT ONE THING.

00:09.477 --> 00:11.276
EVERYONE IS GONNA BE WELCOMED
AT THE HOSPITAL.

00:11.278 --> 00:14.013
WE HAVE THE CAFETERIA ALLOWING
EVERYONE TO PAY BY CHECK.

00:14.015 --> 00:17.016
AND EVERYONE IS GETTING
A BOX SET OF "THE MENTALIST."

00:17.018 --> 00:18.584
WOW.
SY MITTLEMAN.

00:18.586 --> 00:21.720
HEY, I'D LOVE FOR YOU TO MEET
MY GRANDPA AND GRANDMA RICHIE.

00:21.722 --> 00:23.822
GRANDPA RICHIE
IS A VASCULAR SURGEON.

00:23.824 --> 00:27.559
THORACIC SURGEON,
JUST TO BE CLEAR AND CORRECT.

00:27.561 --> 00:29.495
WONDERFUL!

00:30.263 --> 00:33.132
SY! THESE ARE MY GRANDPARENTS,
SAM AND EDITH.

00:33.134 --> 00:35.667
I JUST CALL 'EM
MY WHAMMY AND GRUMPA.

00:35.669 --> 00:37.936
WONDERFUL!
SY, SY.

00:37.938 --> 00:39.238
THIS IS
MY UMI AND POOPAH.

00:39.240 --> 00:41.507
THIS IS
MY BUBBIE AND SHITSTAIN.

00:41.509 --> 00:43.976
THIS IS CANADA WET
AND BADUMPBUMP.

00:43.978 --> 00:45.177
WONDERFUL!

00:45.179 --> 00:46.712
SY.
HELLO.

00:46.714 --> 00:49.448
I WANT YOU TO MEET
MY GRANDMA SHIRLEY.

00:49.450 --> 00:50.482
HELLO, FOLKS.

00:50.484 --> 00:52.718
HEART BE STILL,
YOU'RE SHIRLEY JONES.

00:52.720 --> 00:54.353
I'M A BIG FAN.

00:54.355 --> 00:56.155
GREAT,
YOU KNOW HER?

00:56.157 --> 00:59.758
UH, YOU DIDN'T TELL ME YOU HAD
A CELEBRITY SUPERSTAR GRANDMA.

00:59.760 --> 01:00.993
OH, SORRY, CHET.

01:00.995 --> 01:02.628
IT'S JUST THAT
I WAS BUSY SAVING LIVES.

01:02.630 --> 01:05.664
I ONLY HOPE THAT YOU HAVE
THE MOST WONDERFUL DAY HERE

01:05.666 --> 01:06.698
AT CHILDRENS.

01:06.700 --> 01:08.300
OH, I --
CAN I
GIVE YOU A KISS?

01:08.302 --> 01:10.135
YES. OH, YEAH.
NO.

01:10.137 --> 01:11.336
OH, THANK YOU, YEAH.
THANK YOU.

01:11.338 --> 01:13.705
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
WHAT A PLEASURE.

01:13.707 --> 01:15.007
REALLY.
[ LAUGHS ]

01:15.009 --> 01:17.643
BYE.
YOU DIDN'T TELL YOUR CO-WORKERS
WHO I WAS?

01:17.645 --> 01:19.878
WELL, I WANT TO BE KNOWN FOR MY
ACCOMPLISHMENTS AS A PHYSICIAN,

01:19.880 --> 01:22.915
NOT JUST THE GRANDCHILD OF
LEGENDARY ACTRESS SHIRLEY JONES.

01:22.917 --> 01:26.218
OH.
I'M SORRY, CAN YOU JUST DO
A QUICK PICTURE OF US TOGETHER?

01:26.220 --> 01:27.519
[ SIGHS ]
GREAT.

01:27.521 --> 01:28.854
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:28.856 --> 01:30.122
UM...UH...

01:30.124 --> 01:32.658
WHERE ARE
YOUR GRANDPARENTS TODAY, LOLA?

01:32.660 --> 01:34.526
YOU GET INTO A BIG FIGHT
WITH THEM YEARS AGO

01:34.528 --> 01:36.395
AND HAVEN'T SPOKEN
TO THEM SINCE? [ LAUGHS ]

01:36.397 --> 01:38.831
I KNOW YOU MEAN THAT
AS A LIGHTHEARTED JOKE, DORI,

01:38.833 --> 01:41.266
BUT IN MY CASE,
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT HAPPENED,

01:41.268 --> 01:42.734
SO IT KIND OF STINGS.

01:42.736 --> 01:44.069
I'M SO SORRY,
LOLA.

01:44.071 --> 01:45.571
I REALLY
GAFFED THAT ONE.

01:45.573 --> 01:48.173
MY GRANDPA WILLY --
HE USED TO TAKE ME EVERYWHERE,

01:48.175 --> 01:49.675
BUT THEN
WE GOT INTO A FIGHT.

01:49.677 --> 01:51.610
I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHY --
SOMETHING ABOUT A ZIP DRIVE --

01:51.612 --> 01:53.145
AND WE HAVEN'T
SPOKEN SINCE.

01:53.147 --> 01:54.546
THIS IS HIM.

01:54.548 --> 01:56.815
OH!

01:57.884 --> 01:59.618
AND YOU KNOW
THE ONE THING

01:59.620 --> 02:01.487
THAT I WISH
I COULD HAVE SAID TO HIM?

02:01.489 --> 02:03.455
I DO.

02:03.457 --> 02:05.390
ANYWAY,
MUCH WORK TO BE DONE.

02:05.392 --> 02:06.725
YOU KNOW
THE DRILL.

02:06.727 --> 02:09.294
SO, THIS IS
OUR INTENSIVE CARE UNIT,

02:09.295 --> 02:12.264
OR AS WE LIKE TO CALL IT,
NBC's PRIME-TIME LINEUP.

02:12.266 --> 02:14.833
BECAUSE EVERYTHING IN HERE
IS ON LIFE SUPPORT.

02:14.835 --> 02:17.903
AND ALSO, THEY GAVE US
A PRETTY BIG DONATION.

02:19.639 --> 02:21.373
THIS IS SO SAD.

02:21.375 --> 02:23.175
WHAT IF
SOME OF THESE KIDS

02:23.177 --> 02:25.110
AREN'T REALLY
SUPPOSED TO MAKE IT?

02:25.112 --> 02:29.047
WOULDN'T IT SHOW MORE COMPASSION
TO LET NATURE TAKE ITS COURSE?

02:29.049 --> 02:30.415
NO WAY.

02:30.417 --> 02:32.151
I'M AT A TUG-OF-WAR
WITH THE GRIM REAPER,

02:32.153 --> 02:34.086
AND I AIN'T
NEVER LETTING GO.

02:34.088 --> 02:36.455
NOBODY'S DYING WITH DIGNITY
ON MY WATCH.

02:36.457 --> 02:38.524
PERSONALLY,
I'LL BE ENDING MY LIFE

02:38.526 --> 02:40.893
BEFORE IT BECOMES
TOO HARD TO ENJOY.

02:40.895 --> 02:42.427
YOU'D TAKE
YOUR OWN LIFE?

02:42.429 --> 02:43.962
I LIKE
TO CALL IT SELF-RELEASE.

02:43.964 --> 02:47.766
I WANT TO GO OUT ON MY TERMS,
LIKE MICHAEL JORDAN DID,

02:47.768 --> 02:50.235
BEFORE THE WIZARDS,
OBVIOUSLY.

02:50.237 --> 02:51.937
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

02:51.939 --> 02:54.239
OKAY,
RELEASING THE CLAMP.

02:54.241 --> 02:57.509
SUTURE LINES LOOK GOOD SO FAR,
NO LEAKS.

02:57.511 --> 03:00.245
IS THAT REALLY
HOW YOU SUTURE?

03:00.247 --> 03:02.548
♪♪

03:02.550 --> 03:04.616
NO, FORGET IT.
DO YOUR THING.

03:04.618 --> 03:07.186
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
THANK YOU.

03:07.188 --> 03:09.454
[ GROANS ]

03:09.456 --> 03:10.656
HMM.

03:10.658 --> 03:12.791
HA!

03:12.793 --> 03:14.860
NO, JUST -- IT --

03:14.862 --> 03:16.295
YOU KNOW,
IT'S INTERESTING

03:16.297 --> 03:18.163
THAT YOU'RE USING
A PERCUTANEOUS SUTURE

03:18.165 --> 03:21.900
WHEN A, UH, MATTRESS STITCH
WOULD BE FAR MORE EFFECTIVE.

03:21.902 --> 03:26.538
YEAH, IF I COULD JUST, UH --
MOVE OVER, ACTUALLY.

03:26.540 --> 03:28.540
LET HIM IN THERE,
SWEETIE.

03:28.542 --> 03:30.008
OH.
THANK YOU.

03:30.010 --> 03:31.510
[ LIGHT APPLAUSE ]

03:31.512 --> 03:33.745
TELLY SAVALAS HAD THIS BALL
IN HIS HAND,

03:33.747 --> 03:36.048
AND HE THREW IT
RIGHT ON THE GROUND.

03:36.050 --> 03:38.350
AND BOOM,
IT KEPT COMING BACK.

03:38.352 --> 03:40.085
[ LAUGHTER ]
WHAT?

03:40.087 --> 03:41.386
THAT'S SO GREAT!

03:41.388 --> 03:43.322
WHAT A JUICY
HOLLYWOOD STORY.

03:43.324 --> 03:45.057
EXCUSE ME.
HEY, NOT NOW, CAT.

03:45.059 --> 03:46.425
SO, SHIRLEY.
YES.

03:46.427 --> 03:48.927
TELL ME WHAT IT WAS LIKE
WORKING WITH BOBBY PRESTON

03:48.929 --> 03:50.262
ON "THE MUSIC MAN."

03:50.264 --> 03:52.231
I MEAN, HE MUST HAVE BEEN
A REAL CHARACTER.

03:52.233 --> 03:54.233
OH, HE WAS WONDERFUL,
JUST WONDERFUL.

03:54.235 --> 03:55.767
YEAH.

03:55.769 --> 03:57.336
♪♪

03:58.504 --> 04:03.008
OH, MY GOODNESS,
IT'S MY GRANDDAUGHTER, A VISION.

04:03.010 --> 04:04.743
IT'S YOUR
GRANDPA WILLY.

04:04.745 --> 04:07.879
I'M SO SORRY WE HAD A FIGHT,
BUT I'M HERE NOW.

04:07.881 --> 04:09.781
SY, WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

04:09.783 --> 04:13.385
OKAY.

04:15.255 --> 04:18.123
DID YOU EVER RUMBLE
WITH "THE BRADY BUNCH"?

04:18.891 --> 04:23.528
HEY, EVERYBODY, I WANTED TO
INTRODUCE YOU TO MY GRANDFATHER.

04:23.530 --> 04:25.297
OH, HI.
SUCH A PLEASURE.

04:25.299 --> 04:26.598
OH,
BIG OPERATION.

04:26.600 --> 04:28.600
WHAT KIND OF MUSIC
DO WE WANT?

04:28.602 --> 04:30.636
UH, BEETHOVEN,
DIZZY GILLESPIE?

04:30.638 --> 04:33.505
[ PADDLES WHINE ]
OOH,
EARLY SPIN DOCTORS.

04:33.507 --> 04:35.140
[ THUMP ]
THEY ARE --

04:35.142 --> 04:37.442
NO!
GRANDPA, WHAT DID YOU DO?!

04:37.444 --> 04:39.845
OH, GOD.
OH, GOD, GRANDPA.

04:39.847 --> 04:42.147
NO! [ GRUNTS ]

04:42.149 --> 04:44.349
GRANDPA...
DON'T YOU DIE ON ME!

04:44.351 --> 04:46.084
GRANDPA!
[ GASPS ]

04:46.086 --> 04:47.586
WHY WOULD
YOU DO THAT?

04:47.588 --> 04:50.122
I DIDN'T WANT TO TELL YOU,
BUT I'M TERMINALLY ILL.

04:50.124 --> 04:51.690
OH, GOD!

04:51.692 --> 04:54.126
I WANTED TO CASH OUT WHILE
I'M STILL ENJOYING MY LIFE.

04:54.128 --> 04:56.061
OVER MY DEAD BODY.

04:56.063 --> 04:57.829
NOT <i> YOUR</i> DEAD BODY.

04:57.831 --> 04:59.665
OF COURSE
SHE DIDN'T BUY IT.

04:59.667 --> 05:01.466
YOU CAN'T
JUST PUT A WIG ON

05:01.468 --> 05:04.202
AND MAKE LOLA BELIEVE
THAT YOU'RE THE GRANDPA.

05:04.204 --> 05:05.937
ACTING IS <i> REACTING.</i>

05:05.939 --> 05:07.472
TELL ME MORE.

05:07.474 --> 05:09.474
WELL, WHEN I WAS DOING
"THE PARTRIDGE FAMILY"

05:09.476 --> 05:10.876
AT BURBANK STUDIOS --

05:10.878 --> 05:12.177
I'M A BIG FAN.

05:12.179 --> 05:13.378
WE HAD
A WONDERFUL CREW.

05:13.380 --> 05:15.380
ANYWAY, DAVID CASSIDY
HAD THIS SCENE

05:15.382 --> 05:16.948
WHERE HE WAS ALONE
ON THE BUS.

05:16.950 --> 05:19.418
RIGHT.
AND THEY HAD TO GO
ABOUT TWO BLOCKS.

05:19.420 --> 05:21.386
WELL,
THE DRIVER CAME IN

05:21.388 --> 05:24.222
AND DROVE HIM
ALL THE WAY TO PASADENA.

05:24.224 --> 05:26.158
DAVID WAS
THAT COMMITTED.

05:26.160 --> 05:27.426
WOW.

05:27.428 --> 05:29.828
ARE YOU READY
TO GO TO PASADENA?

05:34.600 --> 05:36.935
LET'S GO
TO PASADENA.

05:36.937 --> 05:39.471
I'M GRANDPA WILLY.
WANT TO GO FISHING?

05:39.473 --> 05:41.573
NO, M-MORE DETAILS!
M-MORE HEART.

05:41.575 --> 05:44.576
I'M YOUR GRANDPA WILLY.
LET'S FISH FOR A BIG ONE.

05:44.578 --> 05:46.645
OH, PLEASE, NO.
THAT'S A DETAIL.

05:46.647 --> 05:48.313
YOU -- YOU KNOW WHAT?
I CAN'T DO THIS.

05:48.315 --> 05:49.648
YES, YOU CAN.
NO, I CANNOT!

05:49.650 --> 05:52.517
HI, SWEETHEART,
IT'S ME, GRANDPA WILLY.

05:52.519 --> 05:54.052
BRING IT BACK
TO THE TEXT.

05:54.054 --> 05:56.922
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO FISH WITH ME?
OH, YES.

05:56.924 --> 05:59.024
I'M GRANDPA WILLY.
LET'S FISH.

05:59.026 --> 06:01.960
YES. YOU'LL HAVE HER
FISHING WITH YOU.

06:01.962 --> 06:03.762
I GUARANTEE IT.

06:03.764 --> 06:04.863
[ GRUNTS ]

06:04.865 --> 06:07.699
ALL RIGHT,
IF HE SO MUCH AS MOVES A MUSCLE,

06:07.701 --> 06:09.067
CALL ME,
YOU GOT IT?

06:09.069 --> 06:10.569
OWEN, YOU'RE --
[ MUFFLED TALKING ]

06:10.571 --> 06:12.471
THERE.
THAT SHOULD PREVENT HIM

06:12.473 --> 06:15.941
FROM TRYING TO SWEET-TALK YOU
INTO UNSHACKLING HIM.
BUT LOOK AT HIM.

06:15.943 --> 06:19.745
DO YOU REALLY WANT YOUR GRANDPA
BOUND AND GAGGED IN A HOSPITAL

06:19.747 --> 06:21.213
FOR THE REST
OF HIS LIFE?

06:21.215 --> 06:24.516
I GUESS I DIDN'T REALLY HAVE
A GOOD LONG-TERM PLAN.

06:24.518 --> 06:26.585
IF HE FEELS LIKE
IT'S HIS TIME,

06:26.587 --> 06:28.787
YOU SHOULD RESPECT
HIS WISHES.

06:28.789 --> 06:30.155
YOU'RE RIGHT.

06:30.157 --> 06:32.057
I WAS BEING
SO SELFISH.

06:32.059 --> 06:35.761
I'M GONNA MISS HIM LIKE HELL,
BUT IF MY GRANDPA WANTS TO DIE,

06:35.763 --> 06:37.429
WHO AM I
TO STOP HIM?

06:37.431 --> 06:40.265
GRANDPA?

06:40.267 --> 06:42.167
I FINALLY GET IT.

06:42.169 --> 06:44.035
AAH!

06:44.037 --> 06:45.804
[ MUFFLED SCREAMING ]

06:47.607 --> 06:49.641
GO TO BE
WITH GRANDMA!

06:49.643 --> 06:51.176
YOU TELL HER
I SAID HELLO.

06:51.178 --> 06:52.377
ME!

06:52.379 --> 06:54.279
OWEN!

06:54.281 --> 06:57.416
YOU TELL HER
THAT I AM A GOOD BOY!

06:57.418 --> 06:58.850
[ SCREAMING CONTINUES ]

06:58.852 --> 07:01.686
[ GRUNTS ]
QUIT FIGHTING ME!

07:01.688 --> 07:03.321
DIE WITH DIGNITY!

07:03.323 --> 07:05.257
[ GRUNTS ]

07:05.259 --> 07:07.092
[ SIGHS ]

07:07.094 --> 07:08.827
♪♪

07:08.829 --> 07:11.396
[ SIGHS ]
HE'S GONE.

07:11.398 --> 07:13.698
I MISS HIM ALREADY.

07:15.501 --> 07:18.003
OKAY,
I'LL SEE Y'ALL LATER.
OKAY.

07:19.372 --> 07:22.073
HI, LOLA.
IT'S GRANDPA WILLY.

07:22.075 --> 07:24.242
SY, I APPRECIATE
WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO DO,

07:24.244 --> 07:25.444
BUT I KNOW
IT'S YOU.

07:25.446 --> 07:27.913
PASADENA.

07:28.681 --> 07:33.351
[ Raspy voice ]
HELLO, LOLA, IT'S GRANDPA WILLY.

07:33.353 --> 07:35.187
LET'S GO FISHING.

07:35.189 --> 07:37.489
[ GASPS ]
GRANDPA WILLY!

07:37.491 --> 07:39.191
YES.
IT <i> IS</i> YOU.

07:39.193 --> 07:40.859
YEAH.
OH!

07:40.861 --> 07:41.993
[ SIGHS ]

07:41.995 --> 07:43.962
TELL ME AGAIN
ABOUT THAT FISH YOU CAUGHT

07:43.964 --> 07:44.963
IN LAKE WINNIPESAUKEE.

07:44.965 --> 07:46.364
[ GASPS ]
IT WAS A LAKE.

07:46.366 --> 07:47.599
THERE WAS A FISH.

07:47.601 --> 07:48.934
THAT'S THE STORY,
THAT'S THE ONE.

07:48.936 --> 07:50.702
Sal:
<i>ATTENTION, STAFF.</i>

07:50.704 --> 07:53.472
<i>I'M THINKING ABOUT CHER'S</i>
<i>FORMER BOYFRIEND, GREGG.</i>

07:53.474 --> 07:55.240
<i>THAT IS ALLMAN.</i>

07:55.242 --> 07:57.142
OH!

07:57.144 --> 07:58.343
OH.

07:58.345 --> 08:00.545
I SAW WHAT YOU DID
FOR THOSE TWO.

08:00.547 --> 08:02.214
ARE YOU PROUD
TO BE MY GRANDDAUGHTER NOW?

08:02.216 --> 08:03.582
NO!

08:03.584 --> 08:05.016
I MEAN,
ARE YOU KIDDING?

08:05.018 --> 08:07.352
YOU SPENT ALL OF GRANDPARENTS'
DAY WITH SY AND NOT ME.

08:07.354 --> 08:08.653
I HATE YOU.

08:08.655 --> 08:11.389
YOU CAN'T TALK TO ME
THAT WAY!

08:11.391 --> 08:13.859
I WORKED
WITH BURT LANCASTER.

08:13.861 --> 08:15.494
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]
YOU KNOW THE PLAN?

08:15.496 --> 08:17.829
YOU GOT THE CASH,
I KNOW THE PLAN.
I'LL PAY YOU AFTER.

08:17.831 --> 08:21.166
OKAY, LET'S GET
THIS SURGERY PARTY STARTED.

08:21.168 --> 08:22.601
PATIENT IS UNDER.

08:22.603 --> 08:25.437
LET'S BEGIN.
SCALPEL.

08:25.439 --> 08:26.972
SCALPEL.

08:26.974 --> 08:30.542
[ GRANDPA RICHIE
CLEARS THROAT ]

08:30.544 --> 08:32.943
UH, IS THERE A PROBLEM,
GRANDPA?

08:32.946 --> 08:35.547
UH, JUST PUZZLING
WHY YOU WOULD BEGIN CUTTING

08:35.549 --> 08:37.616
AT THE ENTRANCE
TO THE PYLORIC ANTRUM

08:37.618 --> 08:40.552
WHEN IT WOULD BE MUCH SAFER
TO START AT THE ESOPHAGUS.

08:40.554 --> 08:44.155
OH, UH, WOULD YOU LIKE
TO GIVE IT A SHOT?

08:44.157 --> 08:45.757
H-HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT THAT, EVERYBODY?

08:45.759 --> 08:47.292
UH, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
SHOULD HE GIVE IT A SHOT?

08:47.294 --> 08:48.493
YAY!       YAY!
YAY!                        YAY!

08:48.495 --> 08:49.694
[ APPLAUSE ]
ALL RIGHT.

08:49.696 --> 08:51.263
ALL RIGHT,
THERE YOU GO.

08:51.265 --> 08:54.866
NOW, THEN, NOW, THIS WOULD BE
THE PROPER ENTRY POINT.

08:54.868 --> 08:56.067
OKAY.

08:56.069 --> 08:57.502
BRAZIER CLAMP.

08:57.504 --> 08:59.137
BRAZIER CLAMP.

08:59.139 --> 09:00.338
♪♪

09:00.340 --> 09:03.008
[ GRUNTS ]

09:04.176 --> 09:06.411
HEART RATE IS LOWERING,
DR. RICHIE, THE OLD ONE.

09:06.413 --> 09:07.913
THAT DOESN'T
MAKE ANY SENSE.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.814
W-WOULD YOU LIKE ME
TO TAKE OVER, GRANDPA?
NO!

09:09.816 --> 09:13.585
I KNOW
WHAT I'M DOING.
OKAY.

09:14.754 --> 09:16.254
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
OH!

09:16.256 --> 09:18.723
WE'RE LOSING HER.
PUMP HER
WITH OXYGEN.

09:18.725 --> 09:21.593
GIVE HER A JOLT!
THIS SHOULDN'T BE HAPPENING.

09:21.595 --> 09:23.962
[ GRUNTS ]

09:23.964 --> 09:25.463
♪♪

09:25.465 --> 09:26.898
[ FLATLINE ]
WE LOST HER.

09:26.900 --> 09:28.266
OH!

09:28.268 --> 09:30.769
OH, YES!

09:30.771 --> 09:31.836
YES!

09:31.838 --> 09:35.340
YES, NOW WHO'S
GETTING IT ALL WRONG, HUH?

09:35.342 --> 09:37.342
THAT PATIENT BE DEAD.

09:37.344 --> 09:41.012
ALL RIGHT, GLENN,
YOU HAVE MADE YOUR POINT.

09:41.014 --> 09:44.249
I HAVE BEEN
TOO CRITICAL OF YOU.

09:44.251 --> 09:47.452
NOW I SEE THAT.

09:47.454 --> 09:48.653
THANK YOU.

09:48.655 --> 09:50.655
AND THAT'S
ALL I WANTED TO HEAR.

09:50.657 --> 09:51.990
I LOVE YOU,
GRANDPA.

09:51.992 --> 09:54.125
I LOVE YOU, TOO, GLENN.
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:54.127 --> 09:55.594
THAT'S IT.

09:55.596 --> 09:57.262
THANK YOU.

09:57.264 --> 10:00.165
YEAH.

10:00.167 --> 10:01.600
[ CHATTER ]

10:01.602 --> 10:03.835
<i>ATTENTION,</i>
<i>HOSPITAL STAFF.</i>

10:03.837 --> 10:06.404
<i>MY DOG WAS SHOT</i>
<i>AND KILLED TODAY.</i>

10:06.406 --> 10:09.441
<i>BINGO WAS HIS NAME-O.</i>
<i>THAT IS ALL.</i>

10:09.443 --> 10:11.476
OH.

10:11.478 --> 10:13.578
THANKS FOR COMING
TO VISIT ME.

10:13.580 --> 10:15.180
IT MEANS SO MUCH.

10:15.182 --> 10:17.349
WILLY?

10:17.351 --> 10:18.583
[ GASPS ]

10:18.585 --> 10:20.051
GRANDMA!

10:20.053 --> 10:23.421
I DECIDED TO SURPRISE YOU
FOR GRANDPARENTS' DAY,

10:23.423 --> 10:25.590
BUT THE SURPRISE
IS ON ME.

10:25.592 --> 10:27.158
MY HUSBAND,
WILLY.

10:27.160 --> 10:30.095
COME ON, WILLY,
LET'S GO HOME.

10:30.097 --> 10:31.296
BYE, GRANDPA!

10:31.298 --> 10:33.131
BYE, GRANDMA!

10:33.133 --> 10:34.599
YOU NEVER LET HIM
OUT OF THE HOUSE AGAIN.

10:34.601 --> 10:35.800
